Pr. Will you make the power of God to change the es- sential properties of things, while the things themselves re- main in their true nature? You may as well say, that natu- rally man is a reasonable creature3 but by divine power he may be a true man, and yet want the faculty of reasoning: that naturally two and two make four, but God can make two and two to be joined together in a supernatural manner, so that four shall not result from them; that though, natu- rally speaking, whitewashing a wall makes it look white, yet by an extraordinary power, there may be the presence of all things which make a wall white, yet it shall not do so3 just so it is to make a body present, and yet to have no di- mensions of a body.
